{
  "uuid": "1c6ea59fdb532f3dd8cb77006d9c0f38",
  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Business Development Manager (Contract Logistics)",
  "description": "<h2>Responsibilities</h2><ul><li><p>Identify and develop new business opportunities to drive business growth, with a primary focus on <strong>Contract Logistics and Warehousing services</strong> in <strong>Singapore and Malaysia</strong>.</p></li><li><p>Lead, manage, and build a high-performing <strong>Business Development / Sales team across the SEA region</strong>, including Vietnam, Malaysia, Singapore, Thailand, Indonesia, and Australia.</p></li><li><p>Drive both <strong>short-term and long-term sales targets</strong>, with performance evaluated based on <strong>half-yearly revenue and profit generation</strong>.</p></li><li><p>Actively engage potential clients by providing <strong>competitive and innovative supply chain and contract logistics solutions</strong>.</p></li><li><p>Gather and analyze customers’ logistics and warehousing requirements, and propose <strong>tailored warehousing and contract logistics solutions</strong>.</p></li><li><p>Work closely with <strong>Contract Logistics Innovation and Operations teams</strong> during customer onboarding and solution implementation to ensure successful project delivery.</p></li><li><p>Generate new external business opportunities and manage the full sales cycle for contract logistics accounts.</p></li><li><p>Perform <strong>cross-selling and upselling</strong> of contract logistics and related services to existing customers, where applicable.</p></li><li><p>Prepare, report, and present <strong>sales performance updates</strong> during internal meetings and management reviews.</p></li></ul><h2>Requirements</h2><h3>Education</h3><ul><li><p>Bachelor’s degree or above in <strong>Business Administration, Transportation, Logistics, Supply Chain Management</strong>, or a related discipline is preferred.</p></li><li><p>Proficient in language for business communication; additional language skills are an advantage.</p></li></ul><h3>Experience</h3><ul><li><p>Minimum <strong>10 years of relevant experience</strong> in the logistics industry, with a strong focus on <strong>Contract Logistics / Warehousing</strong>.</p></li><li><p>Proven track record in <strong>new business development and sales account acquisition</strong>.</p></li><li><p>Experience working in a <strong>global or top-tier logistics / forwarding company</strong> is preferred.</p></li><li><p>Demonstrated experience in developing and managing <strong>large-scale, long-term contracts</strong> and <strong>global or regional accounts</strong>.</p></li><li><p>Strong <strong>customer network</strong> in <strong>Southeast Asia and Australia</strong> is an advantage.</p></li><li><p>Knowledge of <strong>supply chain and logistics systems</strong>, such as <strong>WMS, TMS, or related platforms.</strong></p></li></ul>",
